{
  "texts": [
    "Despite these limitations, we have attempted to identify and generalize key trends that emerge from existing research.",
    "Our aim is to provide insights that can guide future developments and highlight promising directions in the field of fossil classification and segmentation.",
    "Deep learning (DL) has the potential to fundamentally transform fossil classification, with CNN-based methodologies becoming established as the most common approach for automated high-accuracy systems in the field.",
    "The widespread adoption of CNNs is driven by their ability to outperform traditional machine learning techniques in capturing complex morphological traits essential for distinguishing fossil taxa across an ever expanding range of fossil groups.",
    "A significant majority of the works employ TL by fine-tuning pre-trained, off-the-shelf architectures like ResNet and DenseNet, enabling these models to generalize effectively even when limited fossil-specific training data are available."
  ]
}